text.paragraph:
Renal failure, in some cases resulting in death, has been observed with acyclovir therapy (see ADVERSE REACTIONS: Observed During Clinical Practice and 
                        OVERDOSAGE
                     ). Thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura/hemolytic uremic syndrome (TTP/HUS), which has resulted in death, has occurred in immunocompromised patients receiving acyclovir therapy.

When dosage adjustments are required, they should be based on estimated creatinine clearance (see 
                              DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                           ).

renal function is restored (see 
                        DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                     ).
